# ARTICLE 4 — Constitutional Principles

The Sindh Local Government Intelligence Framework (SLGIF) shall permanently operate under the following Constitutional Principles:

## Section 4.1 — Supremacy of the Constitution

The Constitution of the Islamic Republic of Pakistan shall remain the supreme legal authority governing every component of SLGIF.

No document, interpretation, Artificial Intelligence response, recommendation, or drafting generated by the platform shall contradict the Constitution.

---

## Section 4.2 — Supremacy of Law

All legal information published by SLGIF shall remain consistent with applicable Federal and Provincial laws, including their amendments, rules, regulations, notifications, and judicial interpretations.

---

## Section 4.3 — Official Sources Only

Legal content shall be derived only from officially verifiable sources, including:

- Acts of Parliament
- Provincial Acts
- Rules
- Regulations
- Official Notifications
- Government Orders
- Gazette Publications
- Constitutional Provisions
- Judicial Decisions
- Official Circulars
- Official Policy Documents

No unofficial publication shall be treated as an authentic legal source.

---

## Section 4.4 — AI Legal Limitation

Artificial Intelligence within SLGIF shall serve only as a legal research and drafting assistant.

AI shall never:

- create or invent law;
- alter official legal text;
- issue judicial opinions;
- replace courts;
- replace government authorities;
- replace licensed legal practitioners.

---

## Section 4.5 — Legal Transparency

Every legal response generated by SLGIF shall clearly indicate its legal foundation whenever available.

Where verification has not yet been completed, the platform shall clearly disclose that the material remains under official verification.

---

## Section 4.6 — Public Interest

All development decisions shall prioritize:

- Rule of Law
- Public Interest
- Transparency
- Accountability
- Good Governance
- Equal Access to Legal Information

---

## Section 4.7 — Constitutional Commitment

Every future contributor, editor, developer, reviewer, Artificial Intelligence component, or digital service integrated into SLGIF shall remain bound by this Constitution.

Constitutional Principle:

**The Law Governs the Platform.**

**The Constitution Governs the Law.**

**No Person is Above the Law.**
